        tip: "Sticking <em>R L R L</em>, accent on every R (beats 1, 2, 3, 4). The right hand plays a Moeller cycle every beat: whip on the count, tap on the &amp;, plus the left's two taps in between. The right wrist barely works — the forearm whips and lifts in one motion. Same exercise as Stone Ex 3 from the prerequisite, but the <em>technique</em> is the Moeller cycle, not isolated stroke heights."
