        tip: "Three conga voices distributed across the kit: <strong>salidor</strong> (low) → kick; <strong>tres-golpes</strong> (mid) → mid tom; <strong>quinto</strong> not yet (next exercise). The cross-stick carries the rumba clave. Three pitches, three rhythmic layers, one drummer. Listen to a guaguancó recording and try to identify each voice — once your ear separates them, the kit translation becomes obvious."
