        tip: "The Bo Diddley beat — Elias McDaniel's 1955 single carried the rumba clave straight into American pop. Hat 8ths instead of palito, kicks fattened up, but the cross-stick still spells out rumba clave 3-2. Once you hear it, you can't unhear it: half the surf records of the 1960s and a chunk of Buddy Holly's catalogue ride this same African pattern."
