        beamGroups: [[2, 8], [2, 8], [2, 8], [2, 8], [2, 8], [2, 8], [2, 8], [2, 8]],
        tip: "Two bars treated as a single phrase. Bar 1 is the basic headbanger. Bar 2 ends with an extra kick on the <em>&amp; of 4</em> — a push into the start of the next phrase. This kind of two-bar shape is how metal builds tension across longer sections; the listener feels the bar 2 push and expects something to land on the next downbeat."
