        tip: "The canonical d-beat. Hat on every 8th, snare on 2 and 4, kick on 1, &amp; of 1, 3, &amp; of 3. Two kick pairs per bar — one in the first half, one in the second. Tempo is ♩=180, fast enough that the 8th-note hi-hat is a real workout. Keep the hat strokes small (1 inch from the cymbal) or your wrist won't last 30 seconds."
