        tip: "Two off-beat kicks: <em>&amp; of 3</em> and <em>&amp; of 4</em>. The bar now has four kick attacks (1, 3, &amp;-of-3, &amp;-of-4) and the second half of the bar gets distinctly busier than the first. That asymmetry is the whole point — bar 1 sets up the groove; the back half pushes harder toward the next bar's downbeat."
