        tip: "<strong>Play the snare hits as cross-stick</strong> — stick laid across the rim, woody click instead of a full backbeat. Same notation as the basic backbeat, completely different texture. The hi-hat 8ths should also drop a notch in volume to match. The whole groove should sit underneath a singer instead of competing with one."
