        tip: "Set a click at ♩=100. Record yourself playing this groove for <em>16 bars</em>. Then listen back. Are the snare hits exactly on the click? Are the hi-hat 8ths even — or do they accelerate after the snare? Does the kick land tight or a millisecond ahead? Most drummers fail this test the first time. <em>Fail it deliberately</em>, then fix what you hear. This is the studio entry exam."
